📚 Course Overview
A comprehensive, project-based curriculum designed to take you from a complete beginner to a job-ready Machine Learning professional. You'll master the essential mathematics, programming, algorithms, and deployment strategies required in the modern AI landscape .

🎯 What You'll Learn
✅ Foundations: Python for ML, Linear Algebra, Calculus, Probability & Statistics 

✅ Core ML: Supervised & Unsupervised Learning, Model Evaluation, Feature Engineering 

✅ Advanced ML: Ensemble Methods, Recommendation Systems, Anomaly Detection 

✅ Deep Learning: Neural Networks, CNNs, RNNs, Transformers 

✅ Specializations: NLP, Computer Vision, Time Series, Generative AI 

✅ Production: MLOps, Model Deployment, Cloud Platforms

Week 1: Python for Data Science & Math Refresher

📋 Learning Objectives
By the end of this week, you will be able to:

✅ Set up a professional Python data science environment

✅ Master NumPy for numerical computations

✅ Use Pandas for data manipulation and analysis

✅ Visualize data with Matplotlib and Seaborn

✅ Refresh key mathematical concepts for ML

✅ Work through a complete Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) project

